Short Title: Child Care Regulatory Reforms & Flexibilities. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MAKE VARIOUS CHILD CARE REGULATORY REFORMS AND PROVIDE
3 FOR FLEXIBILITIES IN SCHOOL-AGE CHILD CARE.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5
6 PART I. VARIOUS CHILD CARE REGULATORY REFORMS
7
8 EXPERIENCE EQUIVALENCY FOR LEAD TEACHERS IN LICENSED CHILD CARE
9 SECTION 1.1. Section 8 of S.L. 2024-34 is amended by adding a new subsection to
10 read:
11 "SECTION 8.(a1) In modifying the quality rating improvement system (QRIS), the Division
12 of Child Development and Early Education shall ensure a North Carolina Early Childhood
13 Credential based on five years of work experience in a licensed child care facility in this State is
14 treated as equivalent to when that credential is earned through other pathways for purposes of
15 awarding a star rating."
16 SECTION 1.2. G.S. 110-91(8) reads as rewritten:
17 "(8) Qualifications for Staff. – Qualifications for child care staff are as follows:
18 a. All child care center administrators shall be at least 21 years of age.
19 All child care center administrators shall have the North Carolina
20 Early Childhood Administration Credential or its equivalent as
21 determined by the Department. All child care administrators
22 performing administrative duties as of the date this act becomes law
23 and child care administrators who assume administrative duties at any
24 time after this act becomes law and until September 1, 1998, shall
25 obtain the required credential by September 1, 2000. Child care
26 administrators who assume administrative duties after September 1,
27 1998, shall begin working toward the completion of the North Carolina
28 Early Childhood Administration Credential or its equivalent within six
29 months after assuming administrative duties and shall complete the
30 credential or its equivalent within two years after beginning work to
31 complete the credential. Each child care center shall be under the
32 direction or supervision of a person meeting these requirements. All
33 staff counted toward meeting the required staff-child ratio shall be at
34 least 16 years of age, provided that persons younger than 18 years of
